
In the following output, "PIPPO" is my attempt at using a struct, ignore it.
"PLUTO" is the raw response so that you can reuse it.


Here vfoA is in normal AM

ik5pvx@penny:~/k3stuff/mem $ ./decode -i 99
Address:    0x24C0
Bytes read: 0x40
Label: _____
